 class="" data-state="closed"><button aria-label="View in full screen" class="flex items-center transition-colors select-none hover:[&amp;_.icon]:text-token-text-primary hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary rounded-full size-9 justify-center p-1.5"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon text-token-text-primary"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-9a8a5f2a.svg#19c64a" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></span></div></div></div></div></div><div class="writing-block-editor markdown-new-styling relative flow-root pt-(--writing-block-editor-pt) pe-(--writing-block-editor-pr) pb-(--writing-block-editor-pb) ps-(--writing-block-editor-pl)" style="--writing-block-editor-pt: 0px; --writing-block-editor-pr: calc(5 * var(--spacing)); --writing-block-editor-pb: calc(4 * var(--spacing)); --writing-block-editor-pl: calc(5 * var(--spacing));"><div class="ProseMirror markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full min-h-6 break-words focus:outline-none" data-writing-block-fullscreen-editor-region="true" data-writing-block-fullscreen-editor-layout="inline" contenteditable="true" aria-disabled="false" dir="auto" translate="no"><p><strong><span>Day 4 – Performance Analytics &amp; Fund Evaluation</span></strong></p><p><span>Today I performed advanced performance analysis on mutual fund datasets using Python, Pandas, NumPy, SciPy, and Matplotlib. The analysis focused on evaluating fund performance, risk, and benchmark comparison metrics.</span></p><p><span>Key tasks completed:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Calculated daily returns for all mutual fund schemes and validated return distributions.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Computed CAGR metrics to evaluate long-term fund growth.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Calculated Sharpe Ratio and Sortino Ratio to assess risk-adjusted performance.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Performed Alpha and Beta analysis against the NIFTY100 benchmark using regression techniques.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Measured Maximum Drawdown to evaluate downside risk.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Built a composite Fund Scorecard (0–100) using returns, Sharpe Ratio, Alpha, expense ratio, and drawdown metrics.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Created benchmark comparison visualizations and calculated tracking error.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Exported analytical outputs including fund_scorecard.csv and alpha_beta.csv for reporting purposes.</span></p></li></ul><p><span>All analysis was documented in a Jupyter Notebook and version-controlled through GitHub.</span></p></div></div></div><div aria-hidden="true" class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 z-2 rounded-[24px] shadow-[inset_0px_0px_0px_1px_rgba(0,0,0,0.07)]" data-writing-block-fullscreen-shell-border="true"></div></div></div>
